Empty Clip - Top-down shooter
by Alan Witkowski

Latest version can be found at:
https://github.com/jazztickets/emptyclip

Linux dependencies:
cmake
sdl2
freetype
openal
libvorbis
libogg
zlib

Building:
mkdir build
cd build
cmake ..
make -j`nproc`

Building in Codelite:
Open codelite/emptyclip.workspace with codelite. Run the custom build target 'CMake', then build with F7.

Installing:
run "sudo make install" from the build directory.

Command-line arguments
-level [.map file]        Test a level
-fullscreen               Run game fullscreen 
-window                   Run game in a window
-w [width]                Set screen width
-h [height]               Set screen height
-msaa [samples]           Set MSAA sample count
-vsync [value]            Set V-sync mode (0, 1, -1)
-noaudio                  Disable audio
-editor [level]           Start in the mapeditor
-mod [mod directory]      Use game data from [mod directory]

Keys
E                         Move Up
D                         Move Down
S                         Move Left
F                         Move Right
Space                     Action button / Pickup item
R                         Reload
W                         Weapon Switch
Q                         Use medkit
C                         Open inventory / Character screen
Left-click                Attack
Right-click               Aim mode
Escape                    Menu (or quit game in test mode)
F1                        Menu
Alt+Enter                 Toggle Fullscreen mode

Save data is in %APPDATA%/emptyclip for windows and ~/.local/share/emptyclip for linux.
